sentences.en: All we can hear is an indistinct crackling, bubbling and hissing.
sentences.cn: 我们所能听到的只是一些模糊不清的劈啪声, 咕嘟声和嘶嘶声.

sentences.en: Everything was ruddy, shadowy, and indistinct to her.
sentences.cn: 每样东西, 在她看来都泛着红光, 显得阴暗而模糊.

sentences.en: Her words were inward and indistinct.
sentences.cn: 她说话声音是低沉的,模糊不清的.

sentences.en: His indistinct speech makes it impossible to understand him.
sentences.cn: 他口齿不清,无法听懂他的意思.

sentences.en: His readings of her seemed now to be vapoury and indistinct.
sentences.cn: 他现在对她的认识似乎是既虚幻而又朦胧.

sentences.en: I had only an indistinct understanding of what was passing around me.
sentences.cn: 我对于周围所发生的事只模模糊糊地知道一些.

sentences.en: I saw other indistinct shapes that stayed out of vision.
sentences.cn: 我看见另有一些模糊的影子晃了一下就不见了。

sentences.en: Looking out over the sea, she descries an indistinct object floating in the water.
sentences.cn: 她向海面望去发现水面上模模糊糊漂着一样东西.

sentences.en: My memory of what happened next is indistinct.
sentences.cn: 接下来发生了什么我都不记得了。
她含含糊糊地嘟哝了句什么。

sentences.en: The air cell partition become indistinct.
The left kidney and psoas shadows may be indistinct.
sentences.cn: 左肾和腰肌阴影可模糊不清.

sentences.en: The lettering is fuzzy and indistinct.
The line between the combatant and non - combatant ship, already indistinct, had almost vanished.
sentences.cn: 战斗舰与 非 战斗舰之间的那种本来已经不十分明显的界线, 这时几乎已不存在了.

sentences.en: The radio program was indistinct because of the atmospherics.
sentences.cn: 由于大气干扰,无线电节目听不清楚.

sentences.en: There is a large indistinct area in the photograph.
sentences.cn: 照片上一大块地方模糊不清.

sentences.en: These energy levels are so numerous as to be indistinct.
sentences.cn: 这些能级如此之多甚至无法区分.

trans.tran_en: an indistinct sound, image, or memory cannot be seen, heard, or remembered clearly
